Description . Paratype with regenerating posterior end consisting of a few small achaetous segments; length 3.2 mm for 13 chaetigers, width 0.5 mm . Preserved material yellowish without colour markings, eyes faintly reddish. Live specimens orange, without colour markings (
Imajima 1966
). Ciliation not possible to assess.

Description . Paratype complete, length 9 mm for 56 chaetigers, width 0.4 mm . Preserved material yellowish without colour markings, eyes faintly reddish. Live specimens orange, without colour markings (
Imajima 1967
). Ciliation not possible to assess.

Reproduction . Schizogamy by anterior scissiparity (
Imajima 1966
) behind chaetiger 16 (n= 1 ).
